-- Amtrak Service North From New York City Delayed After Fire Damages Bridge
-- B y   T h e o   M u l l e n
-- 2010-10-24T18:38:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-24/amtrak-service-north-from-new-york-city-delayed-after-fire-damages-bridge.html
Amtrak rail service between New York
City and Croton Harmon, N.Y. is delayed by overnight damage from
a fire at the Spuyten Duyvil bridge in Manhattan, the train
operator said in a statement.  There is no estimate when full service will be restored,
Amtrak said. Repairs are underway.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Theo Mullen at 
 tmullen11@bloomberg.net  